{
  "files": [
    {
      "repo": "sg-evals/expressjs-express",
      "path": "package.json",
      "version": "0.7.1"
    }
  ],
  "text": "Security audit of Node.js web stack for CVE-2024-47764 vulnerability in the cookie package. Searched all four repositories in the ecosystem for package.json files declaring 'cookie' as a direct runtime dependency. Found one match: sg-evals/expressjs-express (Express v4.21.1) declares 'cookie' version 0.7.1 as a direct dependency in its package.json at line 36. The version 0.7.1 is recent and has the security fix for CVE-2024-47764 (which affected versions prior to 0.7.0). The other repositories examined (sg-evals/nodejs-node, sg-evals/lodash, sg-evals/prisma-prisma) either lack a root package.json, have no dependencies section, or declare cookie-related packages only as dev dependencies (e.g., cookie-es in prisma-prisma's devDependencies), and therefore do not introduce the vulnerability through direct runtime dependencies."
}

